This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with shape exploration, correspondence, abstraction, interpolation, and semantic segmentation from an RGB image. It also mentions the use of implicit surface representation, which is a common technique in computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for learning a general shape template, which falls under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of structured implicit functions, which is a technique used in neural networks (cs.NE).
